 * Sliding Window Rate Limiter for Express.js
 *
 * TRUE sliding window: stores the timestamp of every request per client and,
 * on each incoming request, evicts timestamps older than `windowMs`. The limit
 * applies to any rolling `windowMs`-length interval ending "now" — there is no
 * fixed boundary that resets the counter all at once (which would otherwise
 * permit bursts of up to 2 * maxRequests around the reset edge).
